            <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
                <TITLE>
                    <P>Transfer system inside a dry dilution refrigerator</P>
                </TITLE>
                <CPV_MAIN>
                    <CPV_CODE CODE="38000000" />
                </CPV_MAIN>
                <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SUPPLIES" />
                <SHORT_DESCR>
                    <P>We wish to order two copies of a transfer system inside a Leiden Cryogenics
                        dry dilution refrigerator. We found a company willing and able to design,
                        develop and fabricate such a system. This company is BWI BV. in Leiden, the
                        Netherlands.</P>
                    <P>Based on the requirements and market research we believe that BWI BV is the
                        only company able and willing to design, develop and fabricate the transfer
                        system and that a negotiated procedure is justified. Please see the attached
                        memo for a description of the goal and requirements of the transfer probe.</P>
                    <P>This publication is done to indication of our intention to award the contract
                        based on the negotiated procedure. Other companies can make representations
                        if they don't agree with our decision to use the negotiated procedure.
                        Protests have to made within 20 days after publication by lodging summary
                        proceedings at the Rechtbank Den Haag. Questions can be raised using the
                        Question &amp; Answer module on Negometrix.</P>
                </SHORT_DESCR>
                <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="EUR">324862.00</VAL_TOTAL>
                <NO_LOT_DIVISION />
                <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
                    <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                        <CPV_CODE CODE="38000000" />
                    </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                    <n2021:NUTS CODE="NL" />
                    <MAIN_SITE>
                        <P>Leiden</P>
                    </MAIN_SITE>
                    <SHORT_DESCR>
                        <P>We wish to order two copies of a transfer system inside a Leiden
                            Cryogenics dry dilution refrigerator. </P>
                        <P>The systems consist of a transfer system for a range of scanning probe
                            microscopes and a vibration isolation system that is part of the
                            transfer system:</P>
                        <P>1. The first instrument to be transferred from room temperature to the
                            low temperature stage is a Scanning Tunneling Microscope. </P>
                        <P>2. The system must be compatible with a sample cleaver.</P>
                        <P>3. Further future scanning probe microscopes that need to be transferred
                            are a ‘magnetic resonance force microscope’ and a ‘fiber/tuning fork
                            SPM’.</P>
                        <P>4. The transfer system must be able to transfer an SPM as well as just
                            the tip (or the sample).</P>
                    </SHORT_DESCR>
                    <NO_OPTIONS />
                    <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED />
                </OBJECT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <PROCEDURE>
                <DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
                    <PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
                        <D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                            <D_TECHNICAL />
                        </D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                        <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                            <P>We wish to order two copies of a transfer system inside a Leiden
                                Cryogenics dry dilution refrigerator. We found a company willing and
                                able to design, develop and fabricate such a system. This company is
                                BWI BV in Leiden, the Netherlands. </P>
                            <P>Based on the requirements and market research we believe that BWI BV
                                is the only company able and willing to design, develop and
                                fabricate the transfer system and that a negotiated procedure is
                                justified. </P>
                            <P>The goals of the project are to interrogate quantum materials,
                                devices for quantum computation and experiments that interrogate the
                                foundations of quantum mechanics. To this end we perform scanning
                                probe microscopies at extremely low temperatures. For the STM
                                experiments we strive for an effective electron temperatures of 10mK
                                while for the force measurements in magnetic resonance microscopy we
                                strive for cantilever temperatures down to 2 mK. Both microscopies
                                require extremely good vibration isolation. For the magnetic
                                resonance force microscopy technique the vibration isolation at
                                acoustic frequencies needs to be state of the art. This vibration
                                requirement is especially hard to reach in combination with the
                                required low temperatures.</P>
                            <P>The systems consist of a transfer system for a range of scanning
                                probe microscopes and a vibration isolation system that is part of
                                the transfer system:</P>
                            <P>1. The first instrument to be transferred from room temperature to
                                the low temperature stage is a Scanning Tunneling Microscope. </P>
                            <P>2. The system must be compatible with a sample cleaver.</P>
                            <P>3. Further future scanning probe microscopes that need to be
                                transferred are a ‘magnetic resonance force microscope’ and a
                                ‘fiber/tuning fork SPM’.</P>
                            <P>4. The transfer system must be able to transfer an SPM as well as
                                just the tip (or the sample).</P>
                            <P>See document on Negometrix for further information.</P>
                        </D_JUSTIFICATION>
                    </PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
                </DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
